This week we had our Birthday as a Company!! @the_underdog_project is now 4 years old. These four years lot‚Äôs of things have happened. Good and Bad things. But mostly GREAT things that created memories that will last forever:
Twenty two (22) trophies on the table
(16 in National + 6 in World championships). I think we made a good job so far! - 2019 World Barista Championship 2nd Place
- 2019 Hellenic Barista Championship 1st Place
- 2019 Hellenic Coffee in Good Spirit Championship 1st Place
- 2019 Hellenic Latte Art Championship 1st Place
- 2019 Hellenic Brewers Cup Championship 2nd Place - 2018 World Barista Championship 4th Place
- 2018 World Coffee in Good Spirit Championship 2nd Place
- 2018 Hellenic Roasting Championship 1st Place
- 2018 Hellenic Coffee in Good Spirit Championship 1st Place
- 2018 Hellenic Barista Championship 1st Place
- 2018 Hellenic Aeropress Championship 1st Place
- 2018 Hellenic Aeropress Championship 2nd Place - 2017 World Coffee in Good Spirit Championship 2nd Place

- 2017 Hellenic Coffee in Good Spirit Championship 1st Place - 2016 World Coffee in Good Spirit Championship 1st Place

Two weeks after my second year on the World Coffee In Good Spirits stage and a big trip from Belo Horizonte to Sydney and back I found a trophy waiting for me among the others. And to this success I am not standing alone. So lucky to be part of this amazing team rocking world stages. #theunderdogroasters
It might sound common and outdated but all the people that were by my side all this time need to be mentioned for their support and patience!  @delichristos for trusting me to represent @the_underdog_project again for the second time. @michalis_dimitrakopoulos for supporting me all the way to Brazil. @michaliskatsiavos for his advices at times when things were not perfect at all. And a big round of applause to @gdel_ who was there for me every time I was in need. And last but not least at all I should thank the newest member of #theunderdogroasters @grigoris_mountanos,  the unseen hero. And @finca_deborah for pushing the limits in coffee industry and let me have the opportunity to present this coffee to the world. This not a one man job, this is a result of family work and strong friendship. So Brazil left me with a big smile on my face and stronger than ever. „Éª„Éª„Éª
Greek Barista Champion Michalis Katsiavos hails from the celebrated coffee company, The Underdog, in Athens, which is internationally renowned for the fact that there are 3 World Coffee In Good Spirits Champions on staff. In his very first appearance at the World Barista Championship, Michalis placed fourth in Amsterdam. We interview Michalis at Barista Mag Online today about his experience at the WBC, his work with the team at The Underdog, and his future goals as a coffee professional. On our first ever appearance on World Barista Championship (as our company was est. in 2015) we managed to win the 4th place among 57 countries with our barista champion @michaliskatsiavos . We will put that trophy on our trophy table along with our two world C.I.G.S. and one runner-up world C.I.G.S. trophies. We wanna thank @finca_deborah for such great coffee to be provided to us and offcourse all The Underdogs out there that share our moto:
